# Best Practices

- Reuse expensive, thread-safe helpers instead of constructing them ad hoc in methods or tests.
- For example, when a class needs an `ObjectMapper`, prefer a shared field such as `private static final ObjectMapper OBJECT_MAPPER = new ObjectMapper();` unless a special configuration requires a dedicated instance.
